    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Stoles worn by deacons to designate their rank. In the western church, deacon's stoles are worn over the left shoulder; historically hanging straight down, in the modern church worn across the body and tied under the right arm.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
